						<summary>

						<p>On a hero-stone standing under a <hi rend="italic">bilva</hi> tree.</p>						

						<p>Circa 12th century.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift for heroism, made by the <hi rend="italic">Mummuridaṇḍas</hi> and the eight <hi rend="italic">Hiṭṭus</hi> of Kōḷūru and <hi rend="italic">Mahāmaṇḍālēśvara</hi> Vīra-Hemmāḍi to Rāvai, son of Nāgaiya, probably in appreciation of the heroism shown by him.</p>						

						</summary>
